    "Body": " We are looking for a passionate, high energy and capable individual who has expertise in digital transformation for supply chain, especially in blockchain. An ideal candidate will lead hand-picked team members, cross function stakeholders, and suppliers to define and launch blockchain supply chain use cases. A great opportunity to influence the future technology used to power the Microsoft Cloud! The role serves as a people manager in Cloud Supply Chain organization with key focus areas: Program management of digital transformation for supply chain (33%) Define new supply chain processes with stakeholders for new technologies (33%) Supplier management (software system integrator, external consultancy) (33%) Meanwhile, s/he needs to provide thought leadership and drive strategic initiatives with internal stakeholders and suppliers to support cloud supply chain overall objectives and strategies. Responsibilities To succeed in this role, you must be a thought leader, a driver, and help shape the direction as well as the deliverables for our blockchain strategy for supply chain. More specifically: Program management of digital transformation for supply chain Identify opportunities to utilize new technologies for supply chain Manage pilot and scale up blockchain solution for MSFT cloud supply chain Leverage data in transformation strategy design for supply chain processes Define RFQ / RFP activities in case of using external vendors / consultancy Provide thought leadership and develop operation models to land blockchain Perform required data analytics to support program management decisions Define new supply chain processes with stakeholders for new technologies Work with engineering team, supply chain teams, and other cross functional teams Define required processes due to new technology adoption Drive stakeholder engagement and collaboration in new process development Supplier management (software system integrator, external consultancy) Develop and enable new suppliers Ensure suppliers deliver quality output Qualifications Basic Qualifications: 5-10 years experiences in technology program management BS or Master\u2019s Degree in Computer Science, Supply chain and / or business related field Preferred Qualifications Highly effective communication and collaboration across teams Track record of high-quality, self-directed, timely execution, and attention to detail Understand the technologies e.g. blockchain Extensive experience in leading cross functional teams Cloud / high tech supply chain experience is a plus Exceptional leadership skills and growth mindset in leading a team Distinctive problem solving leadership and analytical thinking for continuous improvement Accomplished skills in data analysis and process mapping, translating data into useful business insights Strong influencing skills and ability to build lasting relationships across multiple layers in the organization Excellent communication and synthesizing skills of both written and verbal Work independently to balance multiple tasks and competing priorities simultaneously Effectively lead cross-organizational meetings to lead teams to consensus and/or decisions to maintain project schedules Exhibit sound judgment in terms of balancing cost and risk Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. If you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or the recruiting process, please send a request via the Accommodation request form. Benefits/perks listed below may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Microsoft and the country where you work. ", 
